-- Ghana 91-day bill yield rises to 25.0241 percent
-- By Kwasi Kpodo
-- Fri Aug 22, 2014 01:14PM EDT
-- None



ACCRA, Aug 15 (Reuters) - The Bank of Ghana said the yield on its 91-day bill rose to a fresh four-year high of 25.0241 percent at Friday's auction, from 24.9903 percent at the last sale.

The Bank said it accepted all 705.29 million cedis ($189.6 million) worth of bids tendered for the 91-day paper. For full details please click here:   http://www.bog.gov.gh/privatecontent/Treasury/Auctresults%201395.pdf